__________('android',)__________


Positive Reviews:

---'if i could have a phone in my watch, i would.the htc aria is the closest next thing.a small phone that has everything: clear calls, fast internet connection, free android apps, fm radio, decent camera.i have had this phone for two years and though i shattered the screen twice and got the phone replaced, this has not been a problem since i installed a screen protector.i you are looking for a phone that will not add more bulk to your life, this is it!' **** 'free'

Negative Reviews:

---"the htc gratia (a6380) runs the more recent android 2.2 rather than 2.1 that runs on the htc aria (a6366)the 600mhz processor inside the htc gratia (a6380) doesn't support adobe flash streaming video unlike the htc aria (a6366)the htc gratia (a6380) supports the wcdma 3g network unlike the htc aria (a6366) which supports the hsdpa 3.5g networkthese two phones are not the same from both a hardware and software perspective." **** 'recent'


